<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN249">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>katirmūk kāral kīḻccēṟ ṟoḷippak</l>
<l>kaṇaikōṭṭu vāḷai mīnīrp piṟaḻa</l>
<l>verippūm paḻaṉa nerittuṭaṉ valaiña</l>
<l>rarikkuraṟ ṟaṭāriyiṉ yāmai miḷirap</l>
<l>paṉainukum paṉṉa ciṉaimutir varālō</l>
<l>ṭuṟaḻvē laṉṉa voṇkayaṉ mukakku</l>
<l>makaṉāṭ ṭaṇṇal pukavē neruṉaip</l>
<l>pakaliṭaṅ kaṇṇip palaroṭuṅ kūṭi</l>
<l>yoruvaḻip paṭṭaṉṟu maṉṉē yiṉṟē</l>
<l>yaṭaṅkiya kaṟpi ṉāynutaṉ maṭantai</l>
<l>yuyarnilai yulaka mavaṉpuka...lari</l>
<l>nīṟāṭu cuḷakiṟ cīṟiṭa nīkki</l>
<l>yaḻuta lāṉāk kaṇṇaṇ</l>
<l>meḻuku māppikaṇ kaluḻnī rāṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l> Yesterday she who is like [this] wide land, (7ab+d)</l>
<l>where, while ear-nosed Āral fish hide below in the mire, (1)</l>
<l>while round-finned Vāḷai fish leap high above the water, (2) </l>
<l>those with nets, crushing together through the paddy field with flaming flowers (3)</l>
<l>so that tortoises [shaped] like harsh-voice Taṭāri drums roll over (4)</l>
<l>draw out bright carp that are like rivalling spears (6)</l>
<l>together with Varāl fish who ripen eggs [shaped] like soft leaves of palmyra, (5)</l>
<l>	would not enter. (7c)</l>
<l>Joining with all the many with chaplets from various places (8)</l>
<l>she was on one way [with them]. Today (9)</l>
<l>[this] girl with a choice forehead and quiet fidelity, (10)</l>
<l>as he entered the world of high standing, (11a-c)</l>
<l>rejects? a place as small as a winnowing fan bathed in itching ashes (11d-12)</l>
<l>[and] with eyes that do not stop crying (13)</l>
<l>smears [its] with cowdung with [the help] of the tears that dim [her] eyes. (14)</l>
</lg>
